<span class="postbody">Haven't really seen any cool robe graphics, but of course you can always use illusion skeleton, wood elf, vah shir, elementals, froglock, scale wolf ect to get some funky clothing effects..  If your a HIE there is a chain tunic you can get made by a smith im thinking its not very expensive and maybe has elven chain or mithril chain tunic something along those lines I cant remember the exact name but i remember selling one to an enc once for his birthday suit.
<br />

<br />

<br />
In terms of good robes some LDoN ones rock. Next to EP robes (drop in potime) they are probably some of the best arround (obviously excluding GoD due to lack of information). Just an interesting side note robe from pon is not that expensive these days and probably well worth the investment. Also watch out for negative cha items its been rumoured for some time it effects mez resist rate (i said rumoured dont flame me) but proven to effect charm duration. Hence diffinately worth trying to find a robe without the negative hit.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
