<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Well, I got enough Essence of Shadow last night to attempt 7 combines.
<br />

<br />
I decided to start with (in this order):  chest, legs, shoulders, arms, boots, wrist, wrist
<br />

<br />
I failed the final combine on the first wrist item, so only ended up with the one.
<br />

<br />
Equipped it all up, and with my old color scheme had a very… disconcerting look going on.  Ran off to snag some dyes and ended up going with the silver look.
<br />

<br />
I’m a bit disappointed, because my one silk bracer is overriding the chain look for the wrist slots, but all in all, I love this look.
<br />

<br />
I also found out, this new Illusion: Look like whatever I want, does not carry across zones.  So, that’s a bit disappointing, but not overly so.  I used the dry bone illusion as my switch over, it’s entertaining watching people double-take as I wander around with “Spellcrafter” for my title, a dual-wielding flaming sword pet, and chain armor.  I must have been inspected 10 times just running around PoK. 
<br />

<br />
So I was just thinking (yeah I’m a bit slow most days) if I were to toss up an illusion before I zone, would it then keep the chain look after I drop the illusion in the new zone?  Hmm… might have to try that out tonight…
<br />

<br />
Thanks for the idea guys, I’m enjoying it immensely.  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_dance.gif" alt="eusa_dance.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
